==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːɡ|-uːɡ]]

=== Noun ===
'''fugue''' ([[fugues]])

# A [[contrapuntal]] piece of music with a fixed number of [[Voice|voices]].  At the beginning of the piece, each voice is introduced in turn by playing a melody, called the [[subject]], after which follows a mix of [[Counter-melody|counter-subjects]], accompaniment passages, periods of [[rest]], and returns to the subject (often [[Transform|transformed]] in some way).
# Anything in literature, poetry, film, painting, etc., that resembles a fugue in structure or in its elaborate complexity and formality.

